overview: >-
  The user initiated a project to develop a web-based sleep questionnaire
  application, requiring database integration for response storage, a
  client-facing dashboard for data access, and authentication middleware. The
  agent began by evaluating the existing codebase against the SOW, identifying
  the need for a database schema for questionnaire responses, API endpoints for
  data capture and retrieval (including CSV export), and an admin dashboard with
  authentication.

  After clarifying user preferences for simple password-based authentication and
  specific demographic data fields, the agent implemented the database schema
  using Prisma with NeonDB, created API routes for saving and retrieving
  responses, and built the admin dashboard. A key decision point arose when the
  user questioned the initial custom HMAC-signed session authentication. The
  agent then pivoted to a simpler, more streamlined approach using Next.js
  middleware for route protection and a basic cookie-based session, reducing
  complexity and improving maintainability.

  Finally, the agent guided the user through the database setup process,
  including environment variable configuration and Prisma migrations, and
  successfully tested the end-to-end functionality of questionnaire submission,
  admin login, and data display/export using the browser tool.
